Isa 5.20 Woe unto them that call evil good, and good evil;

that put darkness for light, and light for darkness;

that put bitter for sweet, and sweet for bitter.

Dear follower of the precious Lord Jesus, we are living in an upside down world that was spoken about here by the prophet Isaiah. This reversal of morality has been the way of the world since the fall of man in the Garden of Eden.

With venom that could not be more evident than if Satan himself were to be incarnated on planet earth, there is a new morality that is spreading its evil wings and spewing out its devilish propaganda like never before. This poison has even infiltrated the ranks of Christendom.

There are alleged Christians who are rethinking the validity and teaching of Scripture. As prophesied in 1 Timothy 4.1, they are a part of the great falling away. They are calling sinful pleasures good. They are calling those who speak out against them, crazy or puritanical. Beloved, Gods morality does not change with the times. Adultery is still adultery, stealing is still stealing and abortion is still murder in Gods eyes.

No matter how the liberal media tries to revise the teaching of Scripture, the word of God does not change. Let God be true but every man a liar. So do not be surprised beloved when people who are deliberately and defiantly living contrary to the clear teaching of Gods Word call you crazy or mad. When the nation of Israel was living contrary to Gods Word, they were saying the prophet is a fool, the spiritual man is mad. There were a group of people who said of Jesus that he hath a devil and is mad.

Beloved, the fallen world that we live in is mad. The new morality of the world is seeking to cover its sinful behavior with a form of godliness that is clothed with a niceness and tolerance for anything but thus saith The Lord. I never knew how wonderful it could be to becalled crazy. May Gods grace fill us with a love for Jesus and His Word for His glory and honor. What and whom the world calls crazy, God calls holy.

